### useStderr() - Write to Stderr Preserving Ink Output

Source: https://context7.com/vadimdemedes/ink/llms.txt

The useStderr hook provides stderr stream and a write function for error output. It functions identically to useStdout but directs output to stderr, allowing for clear separation of informational and error messages in console applications.

```javascript
import React, {useEffect} from 'react';
import {render, useStderr, Box, Text} from 'ink';

function ErrorReporter() {
  const {stderr, write} = useStderr();

  useEffect(() => {
    // Log errors to stderr
    const errors = [
      'Warning: Configuration incomplete',
      'Error: Failed to connect to database',
      'Critical: Disk space low'
    ];

    errors.forEach((error, i) => {
      setTimeout(() => {
        write(`${error}\n`);
      }, i * 1000);
    });
  }, []);

  return (
    <Box>
      <Text>Check stderr for errors</Text>
    </Box>
  );
}

render(<ErrorReporter />);

```

