### Use Focus Hook in Ink Component

Source: https://github.com/vadimdemedes/ink/blob/master/readme.md

Demonstrates how to use the useFocus hook to detect whether a component is focused. Returns an object containing isFocused boolean that updates based on focus state. Useful for rendering different output based on focus status.

```jsx
import {render, useFocus, Text} from 'ink';

const Example = () => {
	const {isFocused} = useFocus();

	return <Text>{isFocused ? 'I am focused' : 'I am not focused'}</Text>;
};

render(<Example />);
```

